# Spec-Driven Cypress Generation

When asked to create or update Cypress tests, treat `specs/*.feature` as the behavior source of truth.

- Start from spec scenarios and map each behavior to focused Cypress test cases.
- Generate files under:
  - `cypress/e2e/` for test suites
  - `cypress/pages/` for page objects when needed
  - `cypress/fixtures/` for deterministic data
- Include positive and negative scenarios from the spec.
- Suggest missing `data-cy` selectors when the UI lacks stable hooks.
- Keep generated outputs modular; do not create one oversized test file.
- Ensure outputs comply with:
  - `AGENTS.md` for project-wide standards.
  - `AGENT-CYRPRESS.md` for Cypress testing/generation standards.

If a feature has multiple workflows, split into multiple Cypress spec files.
